text:
We will now start the test portion

In this experiment you will be presented with 4 letters on each trial. You must memorize all 4 letters.

There will be a short delay, then you will see a cue, either TOP or BOT. This will instruct you to FORGET the 2 letters located at either the top or bottom (respectively) of the screen. The 2 remaining letters that you must remember are called your MEMORY SET. Please forget the letters not in the memory set.

So for example, if you get the cue TOP, please forget the top 2 letters and remember the bottom 2 letters.

After a short delay, you will be presented with a probe. Please indicate whether this probe was in your memory set.

Press the M Key if the probe was in the memory set, and the Z Key if not.

On some trials, you will see a star appear with or shortly after the probe. Do not respond if you see a star. Do not slow down your response to the probe in order to wait for the star.

You will no longer receive the rule prompt, so remember the instructions before you continue. Press Enter to begin.

responses: {"Q0":"I was given a matrix of four letters, two on top and two on bottom. Then I'd get a cue TOP or BOT, if it was TOP, I'd forget the top set and remember the bottom set as a memory set, and if it was BOT, then I forgot the bottom ones and remembered the top ones as a memory set. Then, i'd get shown a random letter and if it matched one in my memory set, I'd press \"M,\" and if it didn't match, then I pressed \"Z.\" If a star appeared around the letter, then i was not supposed to press anything.","Q1":"This was by far the worst task in this study. There were way too many trials at 10. Also, something was horribly wrong with the feedback telling me that I was pressing too slowly on all of them when I was pressing as quickly as I did on other trials and on the practice. That kind of messed with my accuracy in a few trials with trying to press quicker while trying to be accurate but struggling with the stars, but the too slowly feedback was on all 10. That indicates to me that something is wrong with that feedback on this task because there's no way with as quickly as I was pressing that I would be too slow on every single trial."}
